BIB                 11         22
TITLE      Analysis of alpha induced secondary proton production
            in natNi-reactor structural material
AUTHOR     (S.Balakrishnan, M.M.Musthafa, C.V.Midhun, H.G.Das,
           T.T.V.Thaslim, F.S.Shana, T.Najmunnisa, N.T.Rijin,
           S.Ghugre, S.Dasgupta, J.Datta)
INSTITUTE  (3INDCCT,3INDVEC)
           (3INDIND) Jain University, Banglore, Karnataka
           (3INDIND) UGC-DAE-Consortium for Scientific Research
            Kolkata
REFERENCE  (J,ARI,225,111986,2025)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3INDVEC) K-130 Cyclotron facility
SAMPLE     Natural Ni (~45 mg/cm2 thick, purity 99.99%)
            prepared by rolling method
DETECTOR   (HPGE) 100 cc detector, which has an energy resolution
            ~0.37% at 344.27 keV.
METHOD     (ACTIV,STTA) Stacked-foil activation using 30 MeV and
            40 MeV alpha-beams at 100 nA, followed by
            gamma-spectrometry for cross-section measurement.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information on the source of uncertainty
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by S.Balakrishnan (2025-10-18)
           (TABLE,,S.Balakrishnan+,J,ARI,225,111986,2025) Table 2
HISTORY    (20251016C) VT
